  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Exact Sciences?",
  "response": "Okay, here's a breakdown of things new employees at Exact Sciences should know going into their first day, covering practicalities, expectations, and company culture:\n\n**Before Your First Day:**\n\n*   **Review Your Offer Letter and Onboarding Materials:** Make sure you understand the terms of your employment, benefits, and any pre-employment tasks you need to complete (e.g., background checks, paperwork).\n*   **Plan Your Commute:** Know where you're going, how long it will take to get there, and where you'll park (if applicable).  Account for potential traffic delays, especially in Madison, WI (where Exact Sciences is headquartered).\n*   **Know Your Dress Code:** While Exact Sciences leans towards a more business casual environment, it's best to confirm the specific dress code with your manager or HR representative before your first day. When in doubt, err on the side of slightly more formal than casual on day one.\n\n**On Your First Day:**\n\n*   **Arrival:**\n    *   **Arrive on Time (or slightly early):** Punctuality demonstrates professionalism and respect. Aim to arrive 10-15 minutes early to allow for parking, security checks, and finding the right office.\n    *   **Know Where to Go:** Confirm the location with your manager or HR contact. Exact Sciences has multiple buildings/campuses.\n    *   **Check-In:** Check in with the reception desk or security. Be prepared to show identification.\n*   **First Impressions:**\n    *   **Be Enthusiastic and Positive:** A positive attitude goes a long way.\n    *   **Be Prepared to Introduce Yourself:** You'll likely meet many new people. Have a brief, professional introduction ready (name, role, a little about your background).\n    *   **Listen Actively:** Pay attention to what people are saying, ask clarifying questions, and show that you're engaged.\n    *   **Be Respectful:** Treat everyone with courtesy and respect, regardless of their role.\n*   **Practical Matters:**\n    *   **Office Setup:** Expect to get your workspace set up, including your computer, phone, and access badges. IT support will likely be involved.\n    *   **Paperwork:** Be prepared to complete any remaining HR paperwork.\n    *   **Tour:** Expect a tour of the facilities.\n    *   **Introductions:** Your manager will likely introduce you to your team and other key colleagues.\n    *   **Initial Training:** You'll likely begin some initial training on company systems, processes, and compliance.\n    *   **Lunch:** Ask about lunch options. Will you be going out with your team, or should you bring your own lunch?\n    *   **Parking:** Make sure you understand the parking situation.\n*   **Key People to Connect With:**\n    *   **Your Manager:**  This is your primary point of contact.\n    *   **Your Mentor/Buddy (if assigned):** This person can help you navigate the company and answer your questions.\n    *   **HR Representative:** For benefits, payroll, and other HR-related matters.\n    *   **IT Support:** For technical issues.\n    *   **Team Members:** Building relationships with your team is crucial.\n\n**Company Culture and Expectations:**\n\n*   **Mission and Values:**\n    *   **Understand Exact Sciences' Mission:**  Familiarize yourself with their mission to eradicate cancer and improve lives. This is a central theme in their culture.\n    *   **Know Their Values:** Exact Sciences emphasizes innovation, patient-centricity, integrity, teamwork, and accountability.\n*   **Communication:**\n    *   **Ask Questions:** Don't be afraid to ask questions, even if they seem basic. It's better to clarify things early on.\n    *   **Be Proactive:** Take initiative and seek out information.\n    *   **Communicate Clearly:** Be clear and concise in your communication, both written and verbal.\n*   **Teamwork:**\n    *   **Collaboration is Key:** Exact Sciences emphasizes teamwork and collaboration.\n    *   **Be a Team Player:** Be willing to help your colleagues and contribute to the team's success.\n*   **Learning and Development:**\n    *   **Embrace Learning:** Exact Sciences encourages continuous learning and development.\n    *   **Seek Opportunities to Grow:** Look for opportunities to expand your skills and knowledge.\n*   **Compliance:**\n    *   **Adhere to Policies:** Follow all company policies and procedures, especially those related to ethics, compliance, and patient privacy.\n    *   **HIPAA:** Given the healthcare focus, HIPAA compliance is paramount.\n*   **Innovation:**\n    *   **Be Open to New Ideas:** Exact Sciences values innovation and encourages employees to share their ideas.\n    *   **Embrace Change:** Be adaptable and willing to embrace change.\n\n**Questions to Ask (Appropriately):**\n\n*   What are the team's immediate priorities?\n*   What are the key performance indicators (KPIs) for my role?\n*   What are the opportunities for professional development?\n*   What are the team's communication norms (e.g., preferred communication channels, meeting schedules)?\n*   Who are the key stakeholders I should be working with?\n*   What are the biggest challenges the team is currently facing?\n*   How does my role contribute to the company's overall mission?\n*   What are the expectations for the first 30, 60, and 90 days?\n\n**Important Considerations Specific to Exact Sciences:**\n\n*   **Focus on Cancer Diagnostics:** Understand that the company is dedicated to cancer screening and diagnostics. This should inform your work and interactions.\n*   **Fast-Paced Environment:** Exact Sciences is a growing company, so expect a fast-paced and dynamic environment.\n*   **Regulatory Environment:** The healthcare industry is heavily regulated. Be aware of compliance requirements.\n*   **Patient Focus:** Everything they do is ultimately for the benefit of patients. Keep that in mind.\n*   **Madison, WI Culture:** If you're new to Madison, be aware that it has a unique culture.  It's generally a friendly, outdoorsy, and progressive city. Embrace it!\n*   **Cologuard:**  Be prepared to talk about Cologuard, their flagship product.\n\n**After Your First Day:**\n\n*   **Reflect:** Take some time to reflect on your first day. What did you learn? What questions do you still have?\n*   **Follow Up:** Send thank-you notes or emails to those who helped you get settled in.\n*   **Plan for Day Two:** Review your schedule for day two and prepare any materials you need.\n\nBy being prepared, proactive, and positive, you can make a great first impression and set yourself up for success at Exact Sciences. Good luck!\n",
